TY  - JOUR
AU  - Fehr, Ernst
AU  - Kirchsteiger, Georg
AU  - Riedl, Arno
T1  - Does Fairness Prevent Market Clearing? An Experimental Investigation*
PY  - 1993
Y1  - 1993/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2118338
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 108
IS  - 2
SP  - 437
EP  - 459
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper reports the results of an experiment that was designed to test the impact of fairness on market prices. Prices were determined in a one-sided oral auction, with buyers as price-makers. Upon acceptance of an offer, sellers determined the quality of the good. Buyers offered prices that were substantially above the market-clearing level and expected sellers to respond with high quality levels. This expectation was, on average, confirmed by the behavior of sellers. These results provide, therefore, experimental support for the fair wage-effort theory of involuntary unemployment.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2118338
ER  - 



